Demonstrates how to decode an .ASPXAUTH cookie as generated by the current version of Microsoft's implementation of .NET. You should be able to drop this into the `Global.asax.cs` file of an ASP.NET project and be able to share cookies with code running on Mono.

A few notes:
(1) This assumes a machine key section that uses SHA1 validation and AES encryption. It would probably work with other algorithms, but YMMV.
(2) When encrypted, Microsoft includes several bytes of padding (some sort of hash?) on either side of the payload. Presumably, this is to prevent hash collision attacks or something like that. In any case, it means that we can't generate a new ticket with this code, only decode an existing ticket.
(3) ByteUtility.ToBytes is not included here, but it's supposed to take a string of base 16 encoded bytes and return a byte array.
